  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the alternatives to WalkMe?",
  "response": "WalkMe is a digital adoption platform that helps users navigate software applications through interactive guides and on-screen prompts. If you're looking for alternatives to WalkMe, consider the following options:\n\n1. **Pendo**: A product analytics and user guidance tool that offers in-app messaging, walkthroughs, and user feedback collection.\n\n2. **Userlane**: Similar to WalkMe, it provides interactive guides and step-by-step instructions for users, helping them navigate applications seamlessly.\n\n3. **Whatfix**: A digital adoption platform that creates interactive walkthroughs and guides for software applications, along with analytics to track user behavior.\n\n4. **Guided Learning by Articulate**: This tool offers guided training experiences and allows businesses to create custom learning paths for users.\n\n5. **Inline Manual**: A platform that allows businesses to create onboarding tours, tooltips, and task lists to help users learn new software features.\n\n6. **Intercom**: While primarily a customer messaging platform, Intercom offers in-app messages and product tours that can help with user onboarding and guiding.\n\n7. **UserGuiding**: This tool focuses on creating onboarding experiences with tooltips and interactive walkthroughs without requiring coding knowledge.\n\n8. **Intro.js**: A lightweight library for creating product tours and feature introductions. It's more customizable but requires some technical know-how to implement.\n\n9. **Loom**: Although not a direct replacement, Loom can be used to create video guides that help users understand how to use software applications effectively.\n\n10. **SaaS Optics**: This platform is tailored more towards subscription management but includes elements for client onboarding that can help in guiding users.\n\n11. **HelpHero**: A user onboarding tool that offers interactive guides, tooltips, and in-app messaging to facilitate user learning.\n\nWhen selecting an alternative, consider factors such as ease of integration, user experience, analytics capabilities, and pricing structure to find the best fit for your organization's needs.",
